The paper deals with the control and optimization of power systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of chance constraints and heuristics suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.DC). The paper also deals with the use of switchable capacitors and D-STATCOMs, which are devices commonly used in electrical engineering and power systems, suggesting that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of embedded systems (cs.ET) and software engineering (cs.SE).
